            <h2>1. Understanding the Political-Tech Landscape</h2>
            <p>The modern political landscape is influenced heavily by tech giants whose strategies often shape public policy. This section discusses the key elements of these alliances.</p>
            <div class="sub-section">
                <h3>1.1 The Role of Project 25</h3>
                <p>Project 25 aims to create a unified power structure using strategic policy and legislative initiatives. Knowing its framework helps in identifying the intersection of tech and political interests.</p>
                <p>Resources:</p>
                <ul class="resource-list">
                    <li><a href="https://www.propublica.org" target="_blank">ProPublica: Investigative Reports on Political Influence</a></li>
                    <li><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us" target="_blank">The Guardian: U.S. Politics Coverage</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-section">
                <h3>1.2 Tech Billionaires' Influence</h3>
                <p>Tech leaders leverage their platforms to affect public discourse through campaign financing, AI strategies, and social media narratives. This section highlights the impact of their influence.</p>
                <p>Resources:</p>
                <ul class="resource-list">
                    <li><a href="https://www.eff.org" target="_blank">Electronic Frontier Foundation: Digital Rights and Tech Power</a></li>
                    <li><a href="https://www.cfr.org" target="_blank">Council on Foreign Relations: Technology and Power Dynamics</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
